Subject: Military - OLF

Comment: NE NC for 8+ years has been telling the Navy no thank you, we do not wish to host an OLF training facility for the operational flexibility and noise mitigation that will benefit Oceana residence in Virginia. The Navy has not provided a need based argument that supports condemning a community in our state. We have been under the threat of this condemnation and have actually had/have a Record of Decision by our Navy to condemn 30,000+ acres of land in Washington and Beaufort Counties. The Navy should have a similar ROD around Oceana if they are making decisions uniformly across the several states. In 2005-2006 time frame you made a comment something along the line of an OLF should not be forced on any community. I believe you where the 1st senior representative to make a statement along those lines. Is that an accurate assessment of your stance regarding this OLF? If it is accurate, will you please explain to the Navy that their practice of changing their requirements or their story has got to stop. The people of NE NC have very little confidence in what the Navy is telling us now. The Navy will not talk with us in an open forum. The Navy will not show how the two sites, Camden and Gates County where chosen as finalists for this current NEPA process. The Navy cannot provide a need based statement backed with any kind of facts or scenarios that support them even looking at NE NC. The rational for coming to the region is for the benefit of Virginia residence. I understand the importance of the training an OLF does for our pilots. I feel I understand it better then the Navy does. The Navy insists that all 4 sites must be utilized to perform these training missions. The Navy is only concerned with a proper training facility at the 2nd OLF site. The Navy is willing to usurp the police authority of the local governments in our state by condemning properties but will not do that around Oceana. If the Navy was serious about preserving Oceana they would be condemning properties and would have been doing it since 2003. They have not. In fact, they are requiring the cities supporting their Oceana runways to support the mission. The Navy has indicated that it is unsafe and living in the higher noise zones is incompatible with the mission of fighter jet training. As evident by the Harrier crash, the F/A-18 crash near Miramar and the practice bomb that dropped around Oceana in Fall 2007, the Navy is correct. They must have a airfields free of incompatible development. The only problem is the Navy will only do this in North Carolina if one of our two sites is the preferred site. The Navy showed us what should happen around an airfield with their Washington County decision. Condemn properties out to the 60 dB DNL contour line. That same decision must be happening around Oceana, Fentress and NS Norfolk. Failure by the Navy indicates they ARE overstepping their authority and are not making decisions across the several states uniformly. The Navy is claiming they do not have the darkness capacity to perform the training mission in the summertime. The Navy has an agreement that they will curtail, or restrict the same missions they say they do not have the capacity to perform at Oceana. It is my contention that if the Navy flew at their home base and removed the word ALONE in their need based statement found in the Notice of Intent, they would have the capacity needed. The last model the Navy provided us, Alternative 6, the showed that from 10pm to 7 am for the entire year the Navy was going to perform five FCLP operations. This is the same mission the Navy is now telling us they do not have the capacity at Fentress alone in the summertime to perform. In a surge environment, the assets on the entire east coast could be pressed into service to support this 30 day surge. Again, no community in NE NC should be asked or required to host this OLF as the Navy does not have a valid need. For our pilots training, please do not allow the Navy to force this OLF on any community in our State. Why I say for our pilots? If the Navy does not have this 2nd OLF, the Navy will be forced to fix Oceana and fly training missions at that airfield. Oceana should be supporting Fentress. The Navy's argument is they cannot fly at Oceana because of the light and people encroachment so they must have another OLF. The Navy insists our pilots will continue to fly at Oceana, but the training fidelity is terrible at those airfields. For our pilots, the Navy must fix Oceana or abandon the mission. If we give our pilots this OLF, they will still have to perform training missions at Fentress, Oceana and NS Norfolk. Those pilots that have to fly at the old sites will be getting degraded training and will continue to receive degraded training forever. I contend that what will happen is the next BRAC or other capacity determining body will say that the Navy has to many OLFs to support Oceana. Remove one of them. Fentress will be removed. All the training flights from Oceana will then be sent to that 2nd OLF site. The impact will be greater then what is being told to us now. At that time, it will be too late. One of our communities will be forever gone to support the greed and mismanagement of Virginia Cities. My contention is fix Oceana and a 2nd OLF is not required. In their last study, the Navy stated 3 different times in their narrative and numerous times to concerned citizens that Oceana did not require an OLF. I believe them. Because of the history by the Navy of changing their story, it is near impossible to believe what they are saying now. This latest tale by the Navy is an example. Please do not let the Navy take from our County Commissioners the power of directing their respective counties future. The Navy has failed to work with the region. Please require the Navy to work with us, to talk with us, to establish a point of contact with us that is knowledgeable on the subject and who has the authority to tell us the proper story. I ask that a Naval Officer vice a civilian be our liason. The civilian will tell us anything, but the Officer would be honor bound to properly represent the Navy.The Navy's official website for this OLF is pathetic with regard to information on WHY they are putting NE NC through this hell the original 5 sites went through. Please stop the madness. Please politely but firmly explain to the Navy that the people of NE NC understand the importance of the mission they do, but that the Navy has not provided a compelling reason that justifies any community to be forced by our Navy to host this OLF. The region has not provided the Navy with a justification to summarily take the police authority from our local governments. Thank you for your time,

