Dear Governor,

Congratulations on your election! 

I'm writing to respectfully request your help in opposing the U.S. Navy's plan to locate an Outlying Landing Field (OLF) at any of the sites that would create increased military jet traffic over Currituck County, one of the fast growing areas in the country.  I'm sure that you are receiving numerous letters on this subject, so I won't go into great detail about the devastating effects it would have to our economy, ecology and quality of life.  We have only to look North across the Virginia border to Chesapeake and Virginia Beach to see the impact an OLF has on a community.

My family and I support the military mission, but the Hales Lake site is NOT the appropriate solution to the Navy's problem with their Master Jet base and OLF in Virginia.  In Virginia's case, the Navy was there first. 

I moved from Chesapeake, VA to Moyock, NC four years ago to be able to enjoy the quiet, rural surroundings.  I've lived within a few miles of the OLF at Fentress Field some years ago and have endured the nightly touch-and-go's at all hours of the night during the first Gulf War, when the jets were not nearly as noisy as the new Super Hornets.  I was able to move to another location in Chesapeake away from Fentress before eventually coming to Moyock.  

I'm currently a real estate agent licensed, and doing business in both South Hampton Roads, VA and Northeastern NC. This proposed OLF has already had a direct impact on my NC business. I would be closing on a brand new $450K home this Friday in Moyock, if not for the threat that the home will be in one of the noisiest areas of the proposed flight path. Looking at the flight path, finding an alternate site within miles presents the same dilemma. 

I similarly lost a land deal in South Mills, Camden Co. a few months back, while buyers from VA wait to see the outcome of the OLF issue. The final decision is not scheduled until the Summer  of 2010.  It's hard to say what the total impact of the OLF has already presented to our slowed market,  but it certainly hasn't helped and continues to cast a cloud over our market for another year and half. 

Please join our citizens, County Commissioners, State legislators and Congressman in strongly opposing the Navy's consideration of the NC OLF sites that would forever negatively change the future of Northeastern NC.

