Dear Governor Perdue,
I have posted emails on your town forum, and received no information
or contact. To this point your town forum is useless to private
citizens that need your help. I live in Gates County and have been
emailing for help and support opposing the OLF in NE NC. It has been
an ongoing battle since Easley picked our county without our
knowledge, that we were being considered for an OLF. The whole process
from the beginning was unfair and unjust to the citizens of Gates
County. We all know that Washington County was a poor decision by
Easley and the Navy. Once Easley decided to ask for congressional help
to take Washington County off the Navy's OLF , every state department
came forward to find reasons for the poor choice. I do not understand
why Easley decided to " rob from Peter to pay Paul". Every site in the
past and the present have unique qualities and features that clearly
shows an OLF would do considerable harm to the land and it's people.

Gates County has many attributes that should deter an OLF, many of
which the state has used tax payer money to buy and build for the
future. We have Merchant's Millpond State Park, and is currently
building a new visitor center valued over 3 million dollars to
complete. The state last year used tax payer money to purchase the
Chowan Swamp Game Lands along the Chowan River. The purchase was for
over 9,000 acres for conservation and preservation, and intended for
all North Carolinians to enjoy for future generations. There are many
opportunities for tourism and outdoor activities that could be
developed with this large land purchase that would benefit the county
and the state.

North Carolina government seems to want to be a leader in conservation
and moving forward with green projects and good strong growth, but the
left hand does not know what the right hand is doing. Why would we
waste so much money buying and preserving and then turn around and
risk all the good efforts to be impacted? The OLF will not bring good
economic growth to these poor counties, it will only burden and impact
these poor rural counties. The Navy has so many alternatives that
would not impact rural communities, they own many thousands of acres
of land in NC, many abandoned or little used airfields and military
installations. We are asking for you to use your resources and power
to look for alternatives to helping the Navy without impacting these
poor rural counties. Many counties around Cherry Point have indicated
they would welcome the OLF to enhance the military presence in our
state, why are these alternatives not being considered?

This whole OLF situation is about noise, pollution and encroachment
with Oceana in Virginia. The citizens of NC should not be forced to
correct the problems of Virginia Beach and Chesapeake, and poor
planning and control of the Navy. BRAC 2005 decided that Oceana could
house and properly train 8 squadrons without an additional OLF, and
that Cherry Point would receive 2 squadrons. Politics weighed heavily
on that decision, and if Oceana could not provide that training, then
one of the other alternates should have occurred, which could have
resulted more military economics for NC.

The local government and the citizens group in Gates County need your
help and your support. We have been asking for information and a
meeting with you. We need to know your position on the OLF in NE NC.
When you were lieutenant governor you stated you would not support an
OLF in these counties if there was broad local opposition. We have
clearly demonstrated we are totally opposed, and would like the
opportunity to sit at the table and discuss this situation with you.
It is very frustrating for us, we have been dealing with this
encroachment in our lives since September 2007. We spent countless
hours of emails, meeting, phone calls, trying to express our
opposition, and asking for help and support, and now we have new
officials it's like starting all over again. We really need your
attention and help now. I know you have many issues that demand your
time and attention, but we feel this is a large issue that will impact
all of NE NC. I know you are facing many issues with the economy in
our state, but you must realize that Gates County has all the same
issues as all of North Carolina regarding economy and health, but we
have the added burden of loss of homes, farms, inheritance, loss of
wildlife and natural resources that other areas of North Carolina are
not facing.  We are respectfully asking for your help, and hoping you
will make time to visit Gates County to address the officials and
citizens of Gates County. I hope you will find time in the near future
to address the OLF situation in Gates County, and provide transparency
to this issue. Confirmation by you or your staff would be greatly
appreciated.

Sincerely

